<%args>
	$account
	$name => undef
	$circuit_id => undef
	$start => undef
	$end => undef
</%args>
<%init>

	my $switch;

</%init>

	<div class="left huge">

		<h2>Host a tabroom.com tournament</h2>

		<table cellpadding="5" cellspacing="1" width="100%">

			<tr <% ($switch++ % 2) ? "class=\"oddrow\"" : "class=\"evenrow\""%> >

				<th>
					Tournament Name:
				</th>

				<td colspan="3" class="right">
					<form action="deadlines.mhtml" method="post">
					<input type="text" name="name" size="35" value="<% $name %>">
				</td>

			</tr>

			<& /funclib/datepicker.mas, from => "tournfrom", to => "tournto" &> 
		
			<tr <% ($switch++ % 2) ? "class=\"oddrow\"" : "class=\"evenrow\""%> >

				<th>
					Start:
				</th>

				<td class="right">

					<input type="text" name="start" id="tournfrom" size="10" value="<% $start %>">

				</td>

			</tr>
		
			<tr <% ($switch++ % 2) ? "class=\"oddrow\"" : "class=\"evenrow\""%> >

				<th>
					End:
				</th>

				<td class="right">
					<input type="text" name="end" id="tournto" size="10" value="<% $end %>">
				</td>

			</tr>

			<tr <% ($switch++ % 2) ? "class=\"oddrow\"" : "class=\"evenrow\""%> >

				<th>
					Circuit
				</th>

				<td align="right">
					<select name="circuit_id">
%						foreach my $circuit ( sort {$a->name cmp $b->name} Tab::Circuit->search( active => 1, approved => 1)) {
							<option <% ($circuit_id && $circuit->id == $circuit_id) ? "selected" : "" %>
								value="<% $circuit->id %>"><% substr($circuit->name,0,30)." (".$circuit->short_name.")"%></option>
%						}
					</select>
				</td>
	
			</tr>
		
			<tr class="liblrow">
				<td colspan="4" class="right">
					<input class="blue" type="submit" value="  Next: Set Deadlines  ">
					</form>
				</td>
			</tr>
		
		</table>

	</div>

	<div id="rightsmall">

		<p>This area is for tournament directors.  Do not use this form
		if you are trying to register for someone else's tournament.  Go
		back and register for the circuit your tournament is in.  Click on
		your name above to return to the home screen.</p>

		<p>Once you fill in your tournament's information, a request will be
		sent to the administrators of your circuit for approval.  After they
		approve the tournament, it'll appear on the schedule for the circuit and
		be open for registration on the tabroom.com website</p>

		<p>Not all options are covered by the pre-approval forms; be sure to go
		into your tournament once it's approved and create events, rules and
		the like.</p>

		<p>If yours is a standalone tournament without a tabroom.com circuit,
		select High School Invitationals for your Circuit</p>

	</div>

